LAGOS – Comrade Omoyele Sowore, the African Action Congress (AAC) National Chairman, will announce his presidential ambition for the 2023 election this afternoon. Sowore who disclosed this in a special message to his friends and associates, disclosed that the event will take place in Abuja. He said: “Today in Abuja at 12 noon, I will be declaring my intention to run for the position of President, Federal Republic of Nigeria. APC Chairmanship: Stakeholders Kick Against Sen Adamu, Nnamani Ekiti 2022: Segun Oni Storms Ekiti With SDP Flag, Urges Ekiti To… “Venue: Women Development Centre, Opposite Central Bank of Nigeria, Abuja.” Recall that SUNDAY INDEPENDENT had exclusively reported last Sunday that Sowore would be announcing his presidential ambition this week. Meanwhile, all his associates from different parts of the country and party members and supporters are now in Abuja for the epoch-making event.